    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xs-12">
             <h1 class="">Bootstrap Boilerplate</h1>
            <p class="intro">I have created this boilerplate as a starting point for future projects.</p>
            <p class="intro">The default bootstrap grid has been adjusted a little to reduce the gutter-width between columns, which I have always found to be a little wide. Details of this can be seen on the <a href="structure.html">Structure</a> page.</p>
            <p class="intro">I have also created stylesheets for <a href="typography.html">typography</a> and a set of default Navbars. Components will be added as they are created and can be accessed through the UI Menu at the top.</p>
            <p class="intro">The boilerplate has been constructed using <a href="https://codekitapp.com/" target="_blank">CodeKit</a>. <br/>Feel free to <a href="https://github.com/SimonSharville/Bootstrap_Boilerplate" target="_blank">fork</a> it and use as you wish.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div> <!-- / container -->
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xs-12">
            <a href="https://www.simonsharville.co.uk">
              <img alt="Simon Sharville" src="assets/images/Simon_Sharville_icon_600.png" class="ui-profile-image">
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xs-12">
            <h5 class="base heavy ">Simon Sharville</h5>
            <h5 class="light margin-top-5">Graphic Designer</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="container margin-top50">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xs-12">
            <hr class="dashed-client"></hr>
            <p><strong>Note:</strong> Feel free to cut and paste any of the components coding, however, occasionally I have added <strong>ui-classes</strong> to certain elements. These are just for presentation purposes. ie. buttons have ui-btn on them to give them a little vertical space between them. So remove that ui-class when using it.<br/>
            You should also remove the ui-styles.scss from core-styles.scss.  </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
